<html xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      i18n:domain="eea">
<body>

<div metal:define-macro="portlet"
     i18n:domain="eea"
     tal:define="isAnon context/@@plone_portal_state/anonymous;"
     tal:omit-tag="">

<dl class="portlet" tal:condition="not: isAnon">

    <dt class="portletHeader" i18n:translate="">Emails queue (last 24h)</dt>
    <dt class="portletItem">
        <p class="discreet">
            <a class="fancybox" href="http://unicorn.eea.europa.eu/munin/ZopeBackends/Totals/AG_zope_mailqueue-day.png" title="Emails queue (last 24h)">
                <img src="http://unicorn.eea.europa.eu/munin/ZopeBackends/Totals/AG_zope_mailqueue-day.png" style="width:98%;" />
            </a>
            <br />
            <strong>Note: Chart is updated every 5 min, so check at earliest 5 min after you sent the email.</strong>
            <br />
            The chart shows the number of emails in the queue at a certain point of time in the last 24h. 
            When you send an email you should expect a spike in the chart (earliest 5 min after). 
            The spike will decrease as mails are sent until it goes back to 0, which means all mails are sent.
            The emails in the queue are sent slowly to avoid spam blockers. It could take several hours to send many emails. 
        </p>
    </dt>
    <dd class="portletFooter">
        <a href="http://unicorn.eea.europa.eu/munin/ZopeBackends/Totals/AG_zope_mailqueue.html" 
           title="See more historical email queue charts"
           i18n:attributes="title" 
           class="moreLink">
            <span i18n:translate="">More details and history</span>
        </a>
    </dd>
</dl>

</div>
</body>
</html>